    <text id="F0120T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Boyer writes home with news that a friend has been killed. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Written on Envelope: Camp Near Washington, D.C.<lb/> Mr John D Boyer Com B 190
                    regt Pa<lb/> Washington <lb/> Peter Boyer Co C 12 <abbr expan="Cavalry">calry</abbr>
                    <lb/> Washington DC 
                    <name type="recipient">Peter Boyer</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-06-24">June 24, 1863 </date>
                        <name type="place">Camp Near Washington</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear father </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I take up my pen in hand to <orig reg="answer">anser</orig> your kind and welcome
                    letter that came to hand last night and was <orig reg="read">red</orig> with
                        <orig reg="pleasure">Pleser</orig> I was very glad to hear that you are all
                    at Present I also let you know that I am <orig reg="well">will</orig> at Present
                    Time and I hope my few lines will find you and all the rest in good health. I
                    seen state that John Poke was <orig reg="dead">ded</orig> I hope he is in a good
                    place I will stop for this time <orig reg="write">rite</orig> soon </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>to my father </salute>
                    <signed>John D Boyer </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">to my Father </name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
